RT @tibo_maker: Shaan Puri took his Twitter account from 0 to 330K followers in less than 2 years

He's not your average Twitter creator.…

@ShaanVP Thank you for reading.

Hope this thread gives you some ideas for your Twitter growth.

If you liked it then please let your followers find these lessons from Shaan

👉 RT this thread ♻️

Thanks ❤️

https://t.co/fwafJjMMxA

@ShaanVP 10. Validate your product ideas

Twitter is a great place to get traction for your products early on.

You can use it to validate your ideas and even pre-sell your offers.

Shaan did it brilliantly with his Power Writing course - 

https://t.co/EWkFU5YDw7

@ShaanVP 9. Curate cool stuff

If you post the same type of stuff all day, you will bore your audience.

Add more color to your account. Curate interesting articles, podcasts, videos.

And visuals -

https://t.co/jEf6DbNz5J

@ShaanVP 8. Build in Public -

Be open about your work, and share your process with your audience.

Shaan even hires people from within his followers.

And puts out call job post tweets such as this - 

https://t.co/KgfCqAqMCI

@ShaanVP 7. Share wins and losses

Twitter is not just about sharing wins.

Sharing failures makes you more relatable to your audience. 

Shaan shares his best and worst openly on Twitter - 

https://t.co/d4y02vu2TB

@ShaanVP 6. Share your decisions

Many influencers on "business Twitter" only share theoretical knowledge. 

But plain theory isn't very useful for your audience.

Shaan shares his actual business decisions and the reasons behind them. 

https://t.co/CIQADynyMq

@ShaanVP 5. Connect with interesting people

Twitter is a "social" network.

Which means you connect and collaborate with like-minded people. 

And share their work with your audience.

Curating the best accounts to follow is a great way to do this.

https://t.co/9yQzUIQHbJ

@ShaanVP 4. Interesting + Educational content

Your content should be fun but also informative.

Nobody likes only 1 type of content. 

Your audience wants to learn, but without getting bored.

This thread about Instagram food accounts is a great example - 

https://t.co/CmYqAqTbum

Sure I afford the larger payment, but in times of global macro uncertainty, I definitely don’t need it.

3.) Used car values took a nose dive. 8 months ago I had the ability to sell my vehicle for nearly $10k more than I can get for it today.

I was considering putting the funds towards my Model X to equal out the payment.

2.) Living in a one car household within the northeast United States, a winter power outage would put my family at an unnecessary risk of being without car.

With a 16 month old son, that’s a no go.

1.) Timing. I placed the order back in March 2022. @Tesla gave me a delivery timeframe of Jan 2023 and later pushed it to Feb 2023.

On November 28th 2022 I received a text that my Model X was ready for delivery. Clearly I was not prepared.
🧵/ 3 Reasons I decided to put my Tesla Model X order on hold.

We’re now taking the government to court, to stand up for the ocean.  

We need the government to listen. We need the government to protect our seas. We need action, now. 

Read more: https://t.co/k4ZNBHqzss

When the UK Government was writing its latest sewage reduction plan, we highlighted our concerns and offered solutions to adequately protect our ocean from sewage pollution. 

These were ignored. https://t.co/vmbIUJZBSR

@Katiemac221 The plan in question is for England only. We’ve been working on similar problems in Scotland, where our beach cleaners regularly find large amounts of sewage-related pollution. The latest updates on our work in Scotland can be found here: https://t.co/4pBfRUnLs2

What are storm overflows? Why is sewage being pumped into our protected seas?  

Find out how the UK Government is failing our ocean and marine life, and why we’re taking legal action 👇 https://t.co/t8Wjpd06KV

Gadget created to reduce shark bycatch by up to 95%
The battery-powered device called SharkGuard is clipped onto fishing lines, where it emits electrical pulses to deter sharks which approach the baited hooks.
https://t.co/vvkQiQNFha https://t.co/Gf70cBDbCW

Germany calls for ‘precautionary pause’ on deep-sea mining

Marine Conservation Society to take legal action over ocean sewage spills
The co-claimants are calling for the latest sewage reduction plan to be amended to hold water companies to account and protect the ocean from a deluge of raw sewage spillages
https://t.co/0O2BcBXYci https://t.co/tJUz1A9elU

World’s largest seagrass meadow discovered
Cameras attached to tiger sharks in the Bahamas captured the previously undiscovered ecosystem. The meadow, which covers 35,000 sq miles, increases the world’s entire seagrass coverage by over 40%.
